OL,3,CWoman 'searched for husband and son
OL,4,Cfor years' after Omagh bomb
OL,6,F"I'd left their personal belongings,
OL,7,Flike toothbrushes, diaries, etc,
OL,8,Funtouched for many years after the
OL,9,Fbomb. I regularly would have changed
OL,10,Fthe sheets on Bryan's bed, but they
OL,11,Fnever came home, and the silence is
OL,12,Fstill there.
OL,14,F"I've never been to counselling
OL,15,Fbecause I don't see what use it would
OL,16,Fbe if they did not know Fred or Bryan,
OL,17,Fbut I'm also a private person. We were
OL,18,Fjust a very normal family. The three
OL,19,Fof us were very close.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/9
